race.comment: SHAMILIAN MISS (6) jumped favourite at Bunbury last time out and finished off impressively from near the back of the pack. Out to the mile now is perfect and she's unbeaten at this track and trip. Can get to the outside and round her rivals up. SHAZAIR (5) is an exciting mare who looks on the way up. SHe was 2.02L off the winner last time out at Bunbury as favourite, though she drops in weight from that effort and draws better here. Can bounce back to winning ways. OISIN (3) won well two back before a 1L defeat at Ascot most recently. He comes back to the mile today which may hold the key and he has the speed to cross from a sticky gate. Can feature in the finish again. MANZOR MAGIC (4) can improve on the fresh effort.
